init_text:
Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: An audiobook is like watching a movie instead of reading a book.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: While something is read to me, my mind tends to drift towards thinking about other things.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Because of how the sentences are written, while you read them, you can answer questions like who is this person?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: While listening to a book the narrator talk really fast, so I feel as if in order to gain the benefits enjoyed from reading a book, is lost
